likes exist, they too are illustrated. Much fascinating information about Indian uses of native and introduced species is included. The author emphasizes conservation considerations; the aim of the book is to educate the reader about intriguing uses of the plants, and to tell how to gather and use the most palatable and abundant species without damaging the environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCooking (Wild foods)zCalifornia. 0aPlants, UsefulzCalifornia. 0aWild plants, EdiblezCalifornia. 4aIndians. 4aInsecta. 4aanimal sciences. 4abiology. 4abotany. 4aecology. 4aentomology. 4aenvironment. 4aethnic studies. 4ageography. 4ahistory of the Americas. 4ahistory. 4aindigenous peoples. 4ainvertebrates. 4alife sciences. 4aplant sciences. 4aplants. 4apopular geography. 4apopular life sciences. 4azoology. 7aNATURE / Plants / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520905801?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520905801423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520905801/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles